1.  Create VM, set to boot from ubuntu server ISO image.  Do not boot until setting Network to Bridged, copying MAC address and creating Static lease for planned IP.

1.  Install ubuntu server, ensure SSH is installed/enabled

2.  SSH into server and execute these commands:
	> nano setup.sh
	
	Paste contents of setup.sh from this folder - if you want to make changes to the setup script, do it now.
	
	CTRL-X (Y to save)
	
	> sudo chmod +x setup.sh
	
	> sudo setup.sh